

Notes: Linux compile. Requires OpenCV. OpenCV requirements listed at the end.

### Install ### 
# On Linux, navigate to the project directory.
# Type 'cmake .' to create Makefile.
# Type 'make' to compile the code.


### Parameters ###
$ [program] [string: language/commands] [steps]

### Example Commands ###

./langton LR 1000000
./langton RL 1000000
./langton RLR 5000000
./langton LLRR 1000000
./langton LRRRRRLLR 50000000
./langton LLRRRLRLRLLR 5000000

### OpenCV required ###
Required Packages:
GCC 4.4.x or later
CMake 2.6 or higher
GTK+2.x or higher, including headers (libgtk2.0-dev)
pkg-config
Python 2.6 or later and Numpy 1.5 or later with developer packages (python-dev, python-numpy)
ffmpeg or libav development packages: libavcodec-dev, libavformat-dev, libswscale-dev
libtbb2 libtbb-dev
libdc1394 2.x
libjpeg-dev, libpng-dev, libtiff-dev, libjasper-dev, libdc1394-22-dev

http://docs.opencv.org/2.4/doc/tutorials/introduction/linux_install/linux_install.html
